The 2013 Grindhouse blu-ray release of (the Columbia owned) Corruption,
provides home viewers not only with an exceptional transfer of a
UK horror gem, but also presents both the UK/US Theatrical cut AND
the rarely seen, unedited, International (Continental) Version.

The main difference in the releases is the scene with the prostitute, along
with some very short cut-away moments in other 'gorier' scenes. The prostitute
scene in the Theatrical Cut is dialogue based, non-nude and provides a more
intimate kill. Much less 'slasher' than the unedited International Version.
The scene is also played by different actresses for the two versions. In this
version, Jan Waters.

Undoubtedly Peter Cushing's most 'shocking' venture in film and not one that
he was particularly fond of.

